nist-sse pack — content licence
===============================

This pack is derived from:
    NIST SP 800-160 Volume 1 Revision 1 — Engineering Trustworthy Secure Systems
    NIST SP 800-160 Volume 2 Revision 1 — Developing Cyber-Resilient Systems:
        A Systems Security Engineering Approach
    NIST (US Department of Commerce), 2021–2022

Source licence: Public Domain (US Government work, 17 U.S.C. 105)  (tier 1 — see ../../docs/SOURCE-VETTING.md)
No source-material download link is published (see ../../docs/LICENSING.md).

These sources are works of the United States Government, prepared by NIST, and are therefore
NOT subject to copyright protection in the United States (17 U.S.C. 105). NIST's own notice
states the publication "is not subject to copyright in the United States. Attribution would,
however, be appreciated by NIST." They are in the public domain: anyone may reproduce,
transform, and redistribute them for any purpose, including commercially, without permission.

THIRD-PARTY MATERIAL CAVEAT (stated by NIST): both volumes reference and, in places, reprint
material from ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288 and related international standards, which remain the
copyright of their publishers (ISO/IEC/IEEE). That third-party material is NOT in the public
domain. This pack reproduces none of it — it contains only synthesized, transformed reference
notes that NAME the ISO/IEC/IEEE 15288 process groups and describe, in original words, how
NIST augments them for security. The ISO-15288-derived process tables in Vol 1 Appendices
G–K are NOT reproduced here.

Attribution to NIST is provided as a courtesy (see the repository NOTICE), not a legal
obligation. NIST does not endorse this pack or its authors.

